  "rules": [
    "[P1] Distinguish between conditional and unconditional steps before acting.",
    "[P1] Always check for explicit evidence before proceeding with conditional tasks.",
    "[P1] Do not assume the existence of entities without explicit context.",
    "[P1] Do not make assertions about data presence or absence without explicit evidence.",
    "[P1] Only retrieve or calculate information when explicit supporting context is available.",
    "[P1] Withhold answers or actions if required data is not present in context.",
    "[P1] Record exactly the provided measurement and identifiers.",
    "[P1] Do not fabricate or assume details absent from the context.",
    "[P1] Explicitly state when required or relevant data is missing or unavailable.",
    "[P1] Apply protocol-specified thresholds and criteria exactly, without reinterpretation.",
    "[P1] Execute all steps in multi-part instructions, including unconditional actions, regardless of conditional outcomes.",
    "[P1] Mirror the instruction's decision structure and conditional logic in the response, including all conditional branches."
  ],
